Hi 👋🏼 just dropping in to share that today is a great day to ask your loved ones about booking their next cancer screening 💫 Not sure what to screen for? Head to CANCER.ORG and click on Prevention & Screening then •Find Cancer Early• for a guide on screening recommendations by age. Early detection is everything. Think about it like going to a dentist or changing the oil in your car...cancer screening should be a regular part of our lives ❤️ #getscreened

Temporary. Everything. All of it. Even the best of it, especially the best of it. He died at the end of peach season. We spent the summer eating slices of chilled melon together; watermelon, sugar cube, rocky sweet. We made milk bread sandwiches filled with crispy bacon and thick slices of sun-kissed heirloom tomatoes. We ate bowls of cream top yogurt with sweet strawberries, peaches and plums piled high with crushed ice. Just as the summer season faded, he did too. The night before he passed I picked dark purple figs from my mother's fruit trees and we ate them in bed. He smiled all the way up to his eyebrows. Oh this human experience. The love. The joy. The heartache. Pops, I'll miss you every minute of every day. Extra during peach season. 🍑
The sea, the sea 🐚10 years married 💘, my favorite donut, his first corn maze 🌽, the overwhelming generosity of friends, fall apples🍎, dinner dusted in moonlight🌙, the last of the sungolds✨

Grief really is a privilege. Only where there is big love can there be deep loss. What a privilege to have that sort of love. It is not lost on us. 🥹💞To be here and alive there so many feelings. We find ourselves leaning into them even when feeling the aliveness is hard. THANK YOU to all of our family and friends who contributed to our dad's celebration of life. So many generous gestures and moments filled with grace. We are filled to the brim with gratitude. Though we are missing him more than words, we continue to feel his warmth around us🐦‍⬛🌅✨

So many times in life we don't know that the last time we do something or see someone that it is going to be the last. While we can't prevent lasts, we can love what we have now, while it's here, just a little bit more. 💫💫 Say YES to the last minute trip. Stay curious. Remember life is all about showing up. Carry dungy 🦀🦀🦀 home on the plane. Eat jamón in bed. Go out for dinner and share everything you order. Always say YES to the dive bar. 👯‍♀️💖 #havetwinwilltravel #ladyandlarderandfriends

Knowing grief like this changes you. Some days progress with a grey, hazy film on them and others make you pause, seek joy and love extra fiercely because you know it's all fleeting, this human existence. ⚡️Mav has been a part of @ladyandlarder since day one. Forever my little shop bb, my farmers market dream team❤️‍🔥, cheeseburgers by candlelight, sunset walks on dad's favorite beach with marmee, ✨7✨ (although he tried to convince everyone he was 8), Two years cancer-free 🥹, persimmon season, window full of flowers, giant cotton candy, and so much gratitude for cold, salty sea air 🌬️

I read something the other day about gratitude and how you have to think of it like electricity ⚡️⚡️⚡️something that needs to be produced and then expelled 🪄for it to exist 💫 Carrying this close as we head into the final week of a year that has been the hardest (yet) of my 38 on this earth. Still, there's gratitude. So much gratitude. Going to focus on producing and expelling it into existence for the rest of 2023⚡️⚡️⚡️
